HEADWORD: Albeit
<hw>Al`be"it</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>conj.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>al
be</ets> although it be, where <ets>al</ets> is our <ets>all</ets>. Cf.
<er>Although</er>.]</ety> <def>Even though; although;
notwithstanding.</def> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Albeit</qex> so masked, Madam, I love the truth.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

